==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pyrochlore
<hw>Pyr"o*chlore</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Pyro-</ets>
+ Gr. <?/ pale green.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A niobate of
calcium, cerium, and other bases, occurring usually in octahedrons of a
yellowish or brownish color and resinous luster; -- so called from its
becoming grass-green on being subjected to heat under the
blowpipe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pyrocitric</ent>⟦br⟧
